'''''Night Falls Over Kortedala''''' is the second full length release by Swedish pop singer . Announced on ,  and advertised on Lekman's website as a "a collection of recordings 2004-2007",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jenslekman.com/collections.htm | title= Discography - official Jens Lekman website | accessdate= 2007-08-18}}</ref> the album was released in Scandinavia on the label  on ,  and worldwide on , .
The subject matter includes Lekman's first kiss—supposedly at age 19 {{Fact|date=May 2008}}("And I Remember Every Kiss")—and being introduced as the  to her parents ("A Postcard to Nina").
Pre-orders for the Swedish release also include a digital bonus EP, ''Kalendervägen 113.D'', a one track acoustic medley which, according to Lekman, includes "two unreleased songs on it 'The Rain Has Got To Fall' and 'Our Last Swim In The Ocean' as well as a couple of songs from ''Night Falls...'' and a  song from '''' I thought was suitable. It's me, a guitar and a loop pedal, nothing else.  For those of you who prefer it more au naturale."<ref name="Bonus EP">{{cite web | publisher = Jens Lekman | date = August 31, 2007 | author= Lekman, Jens | title = Smalltalk: August 31, 2007 | url = http://jenslekman.com/records/smalltalk.htm | accessdate = 2007-10-26 }}</ref>